==================
|| INTRODUCTION ||
==================

QShaderEditor is a simple multiplatform shader editor inspired by Apple's 
OpenGL Shader Builder. It supports ARB programs, GLSL shaders and CgFx 
effects.

==================
|| REQUIREMENTS ||
==================

You will need at least:

* Qt 5.2
* GLEW 1.3
* CMake 3.0

Optionally, if the Cg (1.4 or above) runtime is found, support for CgFx 
effects will be available.

==============
|| BUILDING ||
==============

CMake is used as the build system. You need to create build directory 
and run cmake:
---------------------------------------
| mkdir build && cd build             |
| cmake -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release .. |
---------------------------------------

The CMAKE_BUILD_TYPE parameter allows the following values:
* Debug: debug build.
* Release: release build.
* RelWithDebInfo: release build with debug information.

For more info about cmake, look at cmake's documentation.

After that run make. You can add -j<number_of_CPU_cores> to speed up the
build process.
--------
| make |
--------

If you want to install QShaderEditor into the system, just run:
----------------
| make install |
----------------

=================
|| DEVELOPMENT ||
=================

The actual repository (rather, this fork) is hosted on GitHub. Latest 
version of the source code can be obtained at:
----------------------------------------------------------
| git clone https://github.com/CheeryLee/QShaderEdit.git |
----------------------------------------------------------

Original source code (by castano-stuff) is deprecated. It is hosted on 
Sourceforge and still can be obtained at:
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
| svn co https://svn.sourceforge.net/svnroot/castano-stuff/qshaderedit qshaderedit |
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

